The caterer initially planned for **18 guests** (half of 36) to each receive **2 hotdogs**, totaling \(18 \times 2 = 36\) hotdogs. When **40 guests** arrived, all received their first choice of **2 hotdogs** (\(40 \times 2 = 80\)). Since there were only **36 hotdogs available**, **40 - 36 = 4** guests did not get a second hotdog.

**Answer:** \boxed{4}

Final Answer: 4

